faz"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 142</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>31</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It corresponds with <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>pakṣa-</w> <gloss><q>wing</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>side</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>flank</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>shoulder</q></gloss></mentioned>, ; <mentioned xml:lang="lv"><lang/> <w>paksis</w> <gloss><q>corner of a house</q></gloss></mentioned>. The word <mentioned xml:lang="ru" dialect="ru-x-novg ru-x-arkh"><lang/> <w>пакша́</w> <gloss><q>left hand</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru" dialect="ru-x-novg ru-x-arkh"><w/> <gloss><q>hand</q></gloss></mentioned>,  may be related to it as well. — Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævvaxs"/> | %iænvaxs%i ‘close’, ‘near’ from %iæm-faxs%i (← %iham-paxša-%i). Cf. also <ref type="xr" target="#entry_faz"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 142</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>31</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>